6:
Whoo-hoo-hoo! Now this is what I'm
talkin' about!
10: Could you keep it down a bit?
15:
Whoops, sorry about that! Forgot
you're not the biggest fan of the
ocean breeze!
18:
But as a man of the sea, I can't help
but let out a yo-ho-ho! You've got
no idea how uplifting it feels for me
to be here!
22:
That reminds me... Don't you plan on
going back to your pirate friends
someday?
32: Nice to see you guys too.
34:
Hey there, didn't expect to see you
two around these parts.
36:
We try to come back every now and
then. Anyhow, is that Hayz you've
got with you?
38:
That's definitely our favorite
loudmouth, Hayz.
42:
Hayz, Hayz, Hayz, you keep repeatin'
that name...
46:
As if he meant somethin' to you.

I don't know any Hayz!
56:
What's wrong?

Aren't those guys your friends from
the Crimson Blades?
60:
Nope, that couldn't be further from
the truth.
67: Not a single one, damn it!
77:
I mean, you're free to believe what
you want. But are you sure you
wanna give your Crimson Blade
friends the cold shoulder?
80:
I can say this much: WE definitely
see you as a friend, Hayz. You came
back for us in the desert—plus you
help out with the dishes sometimes!
90: That really bothered you, huh, Hayz...
91:
I bet you thought we'd abandoned
you.
95:
Ain't that the truth?! You wouldn't
respond no matter how many times
I called you—
97:
Did you by any chance change your
transmitter and not tell anyone?
102:
We can't connect to unverified
devices. Everyone knows that!
103:
We had the same thing happen a
while back too. Did you forget?!
110:
Well, what's it gonna be, Hayz? You
comin' back with us?
116:
You sure you made the right
decision choosing to stick around?
121:
I sure did! After all, I'm the pirate
vanguard of the Crimson Blades'
Starview Branch!
125:
I think you might also be the ONLY
member of this "Starview Branch".
130:
Anyhoo, us bein' mateys is already a
done deal! We're friends forever now!
135:
And to think, just a while ago you
were whining about having no
friends.
141:
You must've heard wrong, 'cuz I'm
definitely not one to whine!
144:
If you say so.

Say, you hand over that flower yet?
148:
You know, it almost feels like you've
been planning things so that you
don't accidentally bump into Marina.
153:
No way, that sounds like something
a total loser would do! And I am NOT
a loser!
163:
What are you laughing at?! Cut it
out!
